  "text": "and play an important role in cell adhesion and recognition. Unnatural sialic acid precursors can be incorporated into cell surface glycoforms by metabolic engineering. [CITATION_1] Direct covalent reactions can also be applied to enable chemical modification of cell surfaces. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] One possible approach is to couple biomolecules of interest to the cell surface via reactive cell surface groups such as aldehydes and ketones. [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] The generation of these reactive cell surface groups may be achieved by direct chemical or enzymatic treatment, or by the metabolic incorporation of an unnatural molecule that contains the chosen chemical species.",
